{"type":"message","id":"041664b2","parentId":"9615c8c0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:57:36.639Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3p2tletql1lf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 115601\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis is done showing 44.8% of invariants are noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending task is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment to compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline. This makes sense given the findings.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at the CFI_RESULTS.md to understand the data\r\n2. Implement a comparison between frequency-based compression and CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. This will test whether CFI filtering actually improves next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action - likely creating a script or document that advances the CFI-weighted compression experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The next logical step is to test whether CFI-weighted compression actually improves next-pulse prediction compared to frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python experiment script that compares frequency-based compression vs CFI-weighted compression for next-pulse prediction, using the invariants.csv data already generated in research/.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nCFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\nCompares frequency-based vs CFI-weighted compression for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport csv\r\nimport random\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\ndef load_invariants(csv_path=\"research/invariants.csv\"):\r\n    \"\"\"Load invariants from CSV.\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    with open(csv_path, 'r') as f:\r\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\r\n        for row in reader:\r\n            invariants.append({\r\n                'invariant': row['invariant'],\r\n                'frequency': int(row['frequency']),\r\n                'cfi': float(row['cfi'])\r\n            })\r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef compress_frequency(invariants, top_k=50):\r\n    \"\"\"Frequency-based compression: keep top-k by frequency.\"\"\"\r\n    sorted_by_freq = sorted(invariants, key=lambda x: x['frequency'], reverse=True)\r\n    return set(inv['invariant'] for inv in sorted_by_freq[:top_k])\r\n\r\ndef compress_cfi(invariants, top_k=50):\r\n    \"\"\"CFI-weighted compression: keep top-k by CFI score.\"\"\"\r\n    sorted_by_cfi = sorted(invariants, key=lambda x: x['cfi'], reverse=True)\r\n    return set(inv['invariant'] for inv in sorted_by_cfi[:top_k])\r\n\r\ndef simulate_pulse_context(invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Simulate a pulse context as a random subset of high-frequency invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    high_freq = [i for i in invariants if i['frequency'] >= 30]\r\n    if len(high_freq) < 10:\r\n        return set()\r\n    return set(random.sample([i['invariant'] for i in high_freq], k=min(15, len(high_freq))))\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(invariants, context, method):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next-pulse invariants given context using given method.\"\"\"\r\n    if method == 'frequency':\r\n        compressed = compress_frequency(invariants, top_k=50)\r\n    else:\r\n        compressed = compress_cfi(invariants, top_k=50)\r\n    \r\n    predicted = context.intersection(compressed)\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef calculate_precision_recall(predicted, actual):\r\n    \"\"\"Calculate precision and recall for predictions.\"\"\"\r\n    if not predicted:\r\n        return 0.0, 0.0\r\n    if not actual:\r\n        return 0.0, 0.0\r\n    \r\n    tp = len(predicted.intersection(actual))\r\n    precision = tp / len(predicted) if predicted else 0\r\n    recall = tp / len(actual) if actual else 0\r\n    return precision, recall\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment(n_trials=100):\r\n    \"\"\"Run compression experiment across multiple trials.\"\"\"\r\n    try:\r\n        invariants = load_invariants()\r\n    except FileNotFoundError:\r\n        print(\"ERROR: research/invariants.csv not found. Run pulse.ps1 first.\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(invariants)} invariants\")\r\n    \r\n    freq_precisions, freq_recalls = [], []\r\n    cfi_precisions, cfi_recalls = [], []\r\n    \r\n    for trial in range(n_trials):\r\n        context = simulate_pulse_context(invariants)\r\n        if not context:\r\n            continue\r\n        \r\n        # Simulate \"actual\" next-pulse as slightly modified context\r\n        actual = context.copy()\r\n        if len(invariants) > len(actual):\r\n            add_inv = random.choice([i['invariant'] for i in invariants if i['invariant'] not in actual])\r\n            actual.add(add_inv)\r\n        \r\n        freq_pred = predict_next(invariants, context, 'frequency')\r\n        cfi_pred = predict_next(invariants, context, 'cfi')\r\n        \r\n        f_prec, f_rec = calculate_precision_recall(freq_pred, actual)\r\n        c_prec, c_rec = calculate_precision_recall(cfi_pred, actual)\r\n        \r\n        freq_precisions.append(f_prec)\r\n        freq_recalls.append(f_rec)\r\n        cfi_precisions.append(c_prec)\r\n        cfi_recalls.append(c_rec)\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"\\n=== RESULTS (n={n_trials}) ===\")\r\n    print(f\"Frequency-based: Precision={sum(freq_precisions)/len(freq_precisions):.3f}, Recall={sum(freq_recalls)/len(freq_recalls):.3f}\")\r\n    print(f\"CFI-weighted:\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:56:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774367856635}}
